reviews.text: This museum gave a very brief overview of the maritime industry in Croatia. If visiting, I suggest purchasing the Dubrovnik card which will allow entry to this and other museums.
An interesting range of exhibits and the museum is worth a visit if you have a few days in Dubrovnik.

This is a nice place to visit if you're on the Dubrovnik Card.
Lots of nice exhibits, takes you back in time though the perspective of the most important trade in Dubrovnik's history.

Worth checking out if you've purchased the Dubrovnik pass, otherwise quite expensive. Lots of interesting maritime history directly related to the area. You're not permitted to take pictures (why?) I still took a couple.. Ssshhhhh ;)
Great presentation in very fitting environment
It's alright, teachers are alright, could be better with the Officer-ship but you can't have everything can you?

Very Unpleasant, My Son went here, it was awful. The food was like something you would see in a prison. Actually, I believe that you get better food in prison.The toilets were disgraceful, it was like they had a rave in there there was some toilet paper stuck to the ceiling.The students there were terrible as they have appalling behavior as they swear wherever they go.Overall I would not recommend this school to anybody not even my worst enemies.
I brutally shot by an SS officer who was situated on top of the car park, this is certainly disappointing, tut tut tut...
My school is great!!!
Students are rowdy on the bus they don't show discipline and they are rude to be beyond belief. They show no respect for others on the bus they are on. It doesn't bode well for the schools  image

This church was built more than 150 years ago and hence has historical significance. Even though it is situated at a crowded junction, you can feel the peace once you walk down the path from the entrance to the church. On stepping into it you get to see a glimpse of an era that has been preserved. The peaceful and holy atmosphere is most evident in the afternoon which was the time I chose to visit it.

Right at the heart of the city, this church is a perfect location for worship. Tree covered campus, ample parking space, neatly maintained gardens and buildings. Church is pretty old, still with the old chairs and benches, same old walls and floor. Under renovation now, a new look is expected.

Resting place for the traffic police men while they're not very busy, a breathing space for them.

It was built in 1851, for the British Regiment stationed in Bangalore. 
Built in the English Renaissance style, the church can accommodate 
700 people and is regarded as the largest "military" church in southern India. 
It has a congregation of over 450 families
The church was consecrated on 25 July 1852 and opened on 8 August, 1852. 
The original estimate of the construction was ₹27,000 (US$380)
After Independence, the church was taken over by the Christian Indian Military personnel 
and their families. It was called Holy Trinity Garrison Pastorate then.
The walls were lined with ornate marble murals and tablets, which spoke about 
great men and women who toiled for the church. They Used to conduct many programs for youth especially Troika. They have a best team for youth. On March 10th they conducted the Peace Rally for the Pulwama Terrorist Attack. Really its a good experience for me. I Love this Church

When I moved to Bangalore, my fiancé was going here so he took me here. It was away from where we stay so we started checking other Tamil places nearby but now we are regularly going there. It’s worth traveling there. Best place to worship, such a nice priest. They have a good worshipping culture. You can feel Almighty’s presence there. #myfavchurch
Always a church with deep history and architecture gives a nostalgic feeling. This Tamil church surely is one of the churches which makes me feel at home and gives me a blessed experience.

Fabulous museum of life in Hull on the streets in the past. Clean tidy and well looked after . it is great that Hull does not charge for admittance 2 it's museums allowing people the chance to see gifts from the past . We took my father in his wheelchair and the place is very disabled friendly . There is a lot to see a few surprises and very nice staff there who are quite informative . There is also a nice little cafe as you approach the museum that does wonderful hot chocolate

Well worth a visit everything from cycles to cars, buses and a train. We took our grandson he loved the old shops, 
 carriages, and horses. 
There were lots of families looking around with it being Easter holidays. Would recommend and added bonus it's free.
Visited this museum with friends for the first time and really enjoyed it. Friendly staff and well looked after exhibits and also free. Loved the street scene.

Amazing and for FREE !! Having taken  a large group of school children there it was really hard to believe  it  was free .So informative  superb exhibits maintained  on the highest level .Information  of  interest and legible for all and for all ages to partake. The movie g stagecraft was one of numerous  highlights of the day. To be fair you could return the  next day and still be enlightened by it all. Whe building  enriched by the cleanliness  and also of the welcoming friendly  informative  staff .Jill Patience

Incredible place we found totally by chance not being from Hull. Really interesting right the way through both floors and learnt so much. Early electric cars, steam cars, bikes, carriages, trams it really is amazing what they have inside. And free of charge although we put an option donation in the bucket. Next time we travel up to Hull this place will 100% be a place to visit.

Absolutely amazing place. We totally loved it here. Staff were really knowledgeable, friendly and helpful. Lifts were busy up to the third floor where it all begins, one was out of action but was pretty quick. You start three stories up and work your way down with lots of slopes for easy pushchair / wheelchair access. 
Cafe was reasonably priced, as was the gift shop.
The main aquarium was such an amazing focal point, seen from all different angles and depths, then to finish off we went into the glass lift which was inside the aquarium! Just magical.
Tickets for the day, but are actually annual tickets so we can return again! So pleased.

Wonderful family day out. Restaurant has freshly made food at affordable prices. All plastic glasses and food containers are made from plant based products. Parking is available at £3 for 6 hours. Easy to find. Pay in to centre once and visit as many times as you like for a year for free. Glass lift gets you closer to the creatures. Staff show you starfish and sea urchins, giving information about the creatures and let you touch them. Very interesting.

I have mixed feelings. The Deep sets out with a clear mission, not for profit, and to be fair it is priced reasonably for all the work they do. They had some really impressive tanks with a great selection but somehow we thought there would be more. The build up is very long and detailed, educational but blending it  (education and tanks) would have been easier on the kids. Lighting was poor on some of the high big signs, we had to use our phone light to see them. Food was well priced in the cafe but kids thought school food was better quality. Sorry. The staff we talked to were brilliant. Very engaging and ready to share their knowledge. We were halfway way when we needed the cafe and a member of staff guided us to a back stage lift and sent us straight up. Can’t fault the staff. And finally, they have electric car charging which meant our car recharged as we explored. A great vision and good effort but some things could be re-thought a bit.

Great set up. Start at top... All walking downhill.
The star of the show is the main tank. Many spots to view.
Parking can be tough if busy. Has a small diner/restaurant area. But many people brought lunch and were eating.
Great for all ages.
Take your time. Many things to see and there are shows at specific times.
Lots of people to answer questions.
And a great gift shop!!!

Lovely visit on mother's Day. Brilliant facilities and great for young kids and not so young kids (adults).

I just wish the food options were less canteen school food feel and more deli style. More healthy and tasty options please rather than fried food
very good
Good bar, cafe serving a wide range of reasonably priced food. Portions were ample and tasty.  Efficient staff and friendly
Enjoyable food, risotto on this occasion. Always have a few good real ales available. Friendly atmosphere and good outside spaces.
A busy place, friendly staff and good service. Had the veretarian and the hot platters to share, excellent value and the food was delicious. Will definitely be returning.

I have visited Larkin's quite a number of times and always found it to be enjoyable. The staff are friendly and efficient. The food is well cooked and very tasty. I definitely would recommend Larkin's to anyone.
great place to meet with friends for a few beers and also family friendly. burgers good
We booked the whole place out and didn't know what to expect. But we had amazing night. Great food, good service and brilliant entertainment. A night to remember. Will diffinately but booking again.

Sat for over half an hour before we even saw a menu. The starters when they eventually came were good but it's not exactly hard to put some sliced meat on a plate, cut up tomatoes and mozzarella and open a tin of artichokes. All down hill from there. They seemed to be having some staffing issues and the under pressure owner was trying to do the meet and greet as well as cook. The bill was reduced to reflect the evening which is fine but doesn't compensate for a spoilt evening. Cannot recommend.

Great food and service but crazy Italian owner!! Had a fantastic meal. Didn't know what we were ordering but owner told us to trust him. Glad we did as one of the best sea food and anti pasta platter we have ever had. Price was very good considering all the food he cooked up. Big up to Lloyd the waiter!

Went today 7 adults and 3 little ones.. highchairs supplied by restaurant .. food was amazing fresh and tasty.. they couldn't do enough for us.. we went as a family and they made us feel like their family.. very welcoming.. we had lobster ravioli..calamari.. ciabatta..fungi tortellini and all sorts.. also deserts and everything was beautiful we will be back
Excellent food and service.   A great atmosphere too. Highly recommend.

A fairly wide range of dishes. Great food. Clean. Staff courteous. The chicken with pepper and black bean sauce was very good. Maybe a wider range of dessert would've helped, but overall a great place to enjoy a meal  with family/friends (as it can get quite loud). Superb value for money. Would recommend !

Good value Chinese buffet with a good range of dishes in the evening. Pleasant and attentive staff. Can get a bit noisy sometimes but only because it is popular and busy. Does what it's designed for if you are hungry for good quality Chinese.

Really nice food. Decent staff, very attentive and good atmosphere.
Slightly cramped in some areas but pretty much something for everyone.

The food was decent but nothing special but it's an all-you-can-eat so you don't expect 5 star cuisine. Me and the Mrs both got up to get some food and when we came back they'd given our seat away. It was hilarious but definitely not good customer service.

Buffet food is poor quality. Staff are rude. 
They only care about your money. 
Do not go there.
No longer Stanleys. Is now a very nice tapas bar
Lovely food, everything freshly cooked and nicely presented, helpful staff. We had fish and chips, smoked haddock croquettes, veggie burger - everything was delicious. Will be coming back.
Good atmosphere. Well cooked food. Polite, attentive staff.
3rd time back here; seafood platter today; just enough to be full but not uncomfortable - perfect for lunch, fresh fish and wife's sandwich and chips was solid and tasty

Ok just about sums this place up... Fried stuff appeared to be all out of the freezer and same with the puds, all bought in.  If you are ok with this, then you are ok here.  Beer wasn't bad, all ok, nothing more nothing less.

Called 300 300 put me through to Wilson Centre enquire about birth certificate and was told i shouldnt have been put through and wouldnt tell me the price of birth certificate and told me id have to go online. Surely it would have taken her 2 secs to tell me the cost of a replacement. very poor
Helpful, Interested & informative
The staff were friendly but didn't really help us. We were no better off after leaving there.
These people are useless, been here countless times and nothing gets sorted. Would have more luck banging my head against a brick wall!
The staff are generally good and helpful but the system can get clogged when busy

Amazing food with great vegan/veggie options. Each time I've been had great food  and the staff are very nice!(the breakfasts are affordable + super yummy!) However I don't recommend the smoothies- but too much apple juice to be considered a smoothie (in my opinion). All in all, great, and affordable place to grab a meal!

 (I reccomend the zoo burger and French toast)

I'd heard good things about this and they weren't wrong! The menu was very good with alot to choose from. Portion size was also very very good. Staff were really friendly and the atmosphere was relaxed. We were a table of 7 and we are thoroughly enjoyed what we had chosen. We weren't waiting that long either. Staff weren't phased by the size of our table, which is refreshing! Will definitely visit again!
Great relaxed atmosphere.  Excellent good. Will be going back xx
Best place to eat during the day. Delicious vegetarian food - and I'm not even vegetarian! Love it!

The Zoo is a hidden gem of vegetarian dining in Hull. Located off the main street if Newland Avenue I would never have even knew it existed if it wasn't for the happy cow app. The portions are large the food is delicious and the service and ambiance are great. Definitely worth a visit if you are in the area. Highly recommended!!

I'll never be back. the staff needs a lesson in manners and customer service. very rude and short tempered people working here. I hope another business is moved into here, because the location is prime. sadly all the other 1 star reviews, which is mainly what this place has, is very accurate. go anywhere except here.
Small spot but great pizza. Reminds me of NY. Atmosphere will certainly take you back some years with the "antique" style decor. Cinnamon knots are a good option as well. Fairly priced lunch special.

Terrible experience!!! I called to place an order and the guy on the phone kept interrupting me and trying to guess my order before I finished saying it. It took him 5 minutes to stop talking and here me say pepperoni and sausage. I asked for 4 of the largest pizzas and I got 4 14 inch pizzas instead of 19 inch.... hours of operation are wrong online and when you call one location and order delivery it automatically reroutes you to another store without telling you which store or why. The person on the phone then gave me a different stories number and when I called and tried to place delivery it was the exact same store. She then told me that they dont do delivery and that it reroutes you to their store... that information would have been useful before you gave me the number and made me call your store again? I'm never eating fuel again! I work for a restaurant as a manager and it's just laziness and incompetence!

Bad. Really bad. We had gotten stuck in traffic and were running behind schedule. We had a 7:30 show to get to around the corner. It was 6:43.  Theoretically,  this should have been plenty of time to eat. I asked the man who took our order if the cheese pizza was ready. He said it was just coming out of the oven. Great. We pay, let the guy know we are unfortunately in a bit of a rush, and take our seat. A guy comes over 7 minutes later with pizza, takes the number off the table, then goes to another table and gives them the pizza. He never brings back our number. 15 minutes goes by and we still don't have our food. I get up to go get it. He gives me the two slices of pizza and wishes me a good night. I asked him about the garlic knots and cookies we paid for. He said oh I'll bring then over. Another 5 minutes goes by and he brings the wrong cookies. Another 5 minutes and we finally get all of our food. I think we finally got all of our food at 7:10. Almost 30 minutes to get two slices of pizza and garlic knots (which were already made and just needed to be heated up). Oh and the food was awful. The "fresh" pizza was luke warm and the cheese was falling off. The garlic knots were just bad as were the cookies that we ate during intermission. I actually felt bad for the two guys working there, because they were the only two employees in the place. One to cook, one to serve, one to take orders, and one to clean.....almost seems like two people can't do everything during dinner time.....

the worst experience I’ve ever had at a restaurant. we arrived at this location at 4:15pm, after ordering and waiting for our food we were told by an employee at 4:45pm that they “did not have cheese pizza ready” and he offered to give us a different kind or we could wait ten minutes for cheese. we decided to wait since we’d already been waiting for over 30 minutes and already paid for CHEESE pizza. about 20 minutes later we were finally served. 

the bathrooms: long story short they were unpleasant. I have been in Gas Stations better then the ones in here. My one specific complaint I will say about the bathrooms was that the height between the floor and the bottom of the stall was was too high. I felt very uncomfortable. All in all worst bathroom I have ever been in.
